Some effective strategies for avoiding copyright infringement include: 
- Properly attributing the work of others by citing sources; 
- Using content from public domain sources; 
- Seeking permission to use copyrighted material from the copyright owner; 
- Using Creative Commons licensed content; 
- Utilizing text-based methods of communication to share information; 
- Avoiding downloading, uploading, and sharing of copyrighted material without permission; 
- Educating yourself on copyright laws; 
- Monitoring the content you share online to ensure it is legal; 
- Utilizing alternative forms of expression such as parody, fair use, and transformative works; 
- Purchasing or renting copyrighted material in order to support the creator; 
- Engaging in peer-to-peer file sharing with a subscription to a legal music or video service; 
- Exploring open source content.
